Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly grease 13x9x2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended. Stir in MINI KISSES Chocolate. Spread batter evenly in prepared pan. Sprinkle nuts over top; press gently into batter. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars.